3":2,"2016-08-05":5}}}},"selected_quotes":["Valley polarisation assisted spin polarisation!"],"citation":{"abstract":"Valleytronics is rapidly emerging as an exciting area of basic and applied research. In two-dimensional systems, valley polarization can dramatically modify physical properties through electron-electron interactions as demonstrated by such phenomena as the fractional quantum Hall effect and the metal-insulator transition. Here, we address the electrons' spin alignment in a magnetic field in silicon-on-insulator quantum wells under valley polarization. In stark contrast to expectations from a non-interacting model, we show experimentally that less magnetic field can be required to fully spin polarize a valley-polarized system than a valley-degenerate one. Furthermore, we show that these observations are quantitatively described by parameter-free ab initio quantum Monte Carlo simulations. We interpret the results as a manifestation of the greater stability of the spin- and valley-degenerate system against ferromagnetic instability and Wigner crystalization, which in turn suggests the existence of a new strongly correlated electron liquid at low electron densities.","altmetric_jid":"4f6fa62f3cf058f610008259","authors":["V. T. Renard","V. T. Renard","B. A. Piot","X. Waintal","G. Fleury","D. Cooper","Y. Niida","D. Tregurtha","A. Fujiwara","Y. Hirayama","K. Takashina"],"doi":"10.1038/ncomms8230","first_seen_on":"2015-06-02T04:46:59+00:00","funders":["niehs"],"issns":["2041-1723","2041-1733"],"journal":"Nature Communications","links":["http://www.nature.com/doifinder/10.1038/ncomms8230","http://www.nature.com/ncomms/2015/150601/ncomms8230/full/ncomms8230.html","http://dx.doi.org/10.1038/ncomms8230","http://www.nature.com/articles/doi:10.1038/ncomms8230.epdf?shared_access_token=x9z4k4N4CTOBlf6uLctK9tRgN0jAjWel9jnR3ZoTv0P1kjqaXAHpYCMQERed6-zXSbDF900KRZqzcD-yhyR22dkxnvP6dNfnD1MeQaf_0BRaaGR1O40XmH2u-_PtGLLfZzTPUKfqP2_i-xo9A6DySa_2sgzOyaiqxgjWgDMIZ4owiEAmld_VIW_